userdoc.notice: Safe ETH and ERC20 transfer library that gracefully handles missing return values.

params.user: The authorized user who triggered the initialization.

claimFees(uint256).details: Accrued fees are measured as rvTokens held by the Vault.

params.sVTokenAmount: The amount of rvTokens to claim.

destroy().details: Caller will receive any ETH held as float in the Vault.

initialize(address,uint160).details: All critical parameters must already be set before calling.

setUnderlyingIsWETH(bool).details: The underlying token must have 18 decimals, to match Ether's decimal scheme.

params.newUnderlyingIsWETH: Whether the Vault should treat the underlying as WETH.

feePercent.details: A fixed point number where 1e18 represents 100% and 0 represents 0%.

isInitialized.details: Can go from false to true, never from true to false.

targetFloatPercent.details: A fixed point number where 1e18 represents 100% and 0 represents 0%.

totalStrategyHoldings.details: Includes maxLockedProfit, must be correctly subtracted to compute available/free holdings.

underlyingIsWETH.details: If enabled the Vault will allow trusting strategies that accept Ether.
